<paragraph blockId="158.[151,1436,1246,1466]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis box="[151,233,1248,1273]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Leaves</emphasis>
veins raised and rectangular in cross-section adaxially; basal pinna 0.7(0.3–1.0) cm wide; apical pinna 0.8(0.5–1.0) cm wide. 
<emphasis box="[423,594,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Inflorescences</emphasis>
prophyll margins without irregular, spine-like projections; flower pits usually spirally arranged, not distantly spaced.
